

                Tech Tip            
By                     
                                    J. D. BIERSDORFER
                            
                MARCH 7, 2018
    
Q. I want to buy a lightweight laptop, but I need to use CDs and DVDs, which none of these models have anymore. Is there any way to still use discs with these tiny computers?
A. When it comes to modern laptop design, many manufacturers have tossed disc drives onto the same pile with floppy drives, Ethernet jacks and other technology considered obsolete — thanks to cloud servers and wireless networks that have taken over a laptop’s data storage and internet connection needs. The quest for smaller, lighter laptops with maximum space on the inside for a rechargeable battery has also pushed out these once-standard computer components.
